entries.meaning: The act of exporting; the act of conveying or sending commodities abroad or to another country, in the course of commerce.
The act of carrying something outside.

(logic) Either the logical law 
  
    
      
        (
        (
        P
        ∧
        Q
        )
        →
        R
        )
        ⇒
        (
        P
        →
        (
        Q
        →
        R
        )
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle ((P\land Q)\to R)\Rightarrow (P\to (Q\to R))}
  
, or the rule of replacement 
  
    
      
        (
        (
        P
        ∧
        Q
        )
        →
        R
        )
        ⇔
        (
        P
        →
        (
        Q
        →
        R
        )
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle ((P\land Q)\to R)\Leftrightarrow (P\to (Q\to R))}
  
.
